1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 Ne4 3. h4 d5 {Black is trying to play positional chess,
without complications..} 4. Nd2 {We want to take his strong, centralized
knight.. Black has 3 options: Nxd2, Nxg5 and Bf5} Nxd2 {Possible move for
black. Now, white has clear situation to play 0-0-0} (4... Bf5 5. Nxe4 Bxe4 (
5... dxe4 {Better is Bxe4, but still, we need to check all options.} 6. e3 h6
7. Bf4 e6 8. g4 Bh7 9. c3 Nc6 10. Qb3 Bd6 11. Ne2 Qd7 12. O-O-O O-O-O 13. Bxd6
cxd6 14. c4 Kb8 15. Nc3 {With better play for white. White is going to play
Bg2 and to create pressure on e4-pawn.}) 6. f3 Bf5 7. g4 Bd7 $2 {Passive move.
Black will have problem with that bishop later. Instructive moment.. We do't
want to waiste time with e3. Instead, we are going to play Qd3 to play long
castle after that. Also, Qd3 is good waiting move, cause we want to play e4
after e6 move} (7... h6 {This is much better move than Bd7. Black wants to
keep his bishop in the play} 8. Bf4 Bh7 9. e3 e6 10. Bd3 Bxd3 11. Qxd3 Bd6 12.
Ne2 Bxf4 13. Nxf4 Nd7 14. O-O-O Qe7 15. Kb1 O-O-O 16. h5 $14 {White is better
thanks to the space advantage. Again, white wants to play e4 or c4 to take
initiative.. By the way, we play h5 again. That's very important move, cause
we freeze black kingside}) 8. Qd3 h6 9. Bf4 e6 10. e4 c6 11. O-O-O Be7 12. Bg3
O-O 13. Ne2 $40 {His light bishop on d7 is a huge problem for him.. We have
very strong attack on his kingside}) (4... Nxg5 {The main move in this moment..
He takes our strong bishop. But, also, he does something else. He opens h-file
for our rook} 5. hxg5 c5 {He is trying to create counterplay in the center and
on the queenside} (5... Bf5 {Logical move.. Black simply develops pieces...} 6.
e3 e6 7. g4 Bg6 8. f4 {c5 is the best move.. Black has to start with
counterattack..} c5 9. Bb5+ Nc6 10. Qf3 {f5 is the threat..} Qd7 {Probably the
best move. Black prevents f5} 11. dxc5 Bxc5 12. Ne2 O-O-O 13. O-O-O Bb6 14. Nc3
Kb8 15. Nb3 {And white is slightly better...}) (5... g6 6. e3 Bg7 7. f4 {With
this move, we gain a space. we have very good, mobile, atacking pawn structure}
c5 8. c3 Nc6 9. Ngf3 O-O 10. Bd3 Qb6 11. Rb1 Bd7 12. a3 cxd4 13. cxd4 Rac8 14.
Kf2 $1 $14 {We don't want to play 0-0. Kf2 is perfect move. Our king is safe
there and rook on h1 is still doing his job- he attacks h7 pawn all the time})
6. dxc5 e5 (6... e6 {Defenitely safer move than e5} 7. e4 Bxc5 8. Ngf3 {We
play almost the same like after e5...} Qb6 {This looks like a dangerous threat.
f2 and b2 pawns are hanging at the moment We don't want to defend any of them.
Instead, we are going to develop pieces...} 9. Bd3 $5 Bxf2+ 10. Kf1 Bg3 (10...
Qe3 11. Qe2 Qxe2+ 12. Kxe2 Bb6 13. Rh4 $14 {Rah1 and Rxh7 threat is unstoppable
}) 11. Qe2 {Black has huge problem.. His d5 pawn is hanging at the moment. If
he play 0-0, his king is in mate nett thanks to opened h-file and b1-h7
diagonal If he takes on e4, we take with the Knight and he has to move his
bishop back, so practically we gain 2 tempis. After that, white will have much
better position Black can't protect d5 pawn properly, so the best move is Kd8}
Kd8 12. c4 $40 {Logical move. We want to open the center and to attack black
king. You can see that white has already developed all pieces. On the other
hand, black developed only his bishop and queen. Besides that, his king is
badly placed on d8}) 7. e4 Bxc5 8. Nb3 Bb6 (8... d4 9. Nxc5 Qa5+ 10. c3 Qxc5
11. cxd4 exd4 12. Rc1 Qa5+ 13. Qd2 Qxd2+ 14. Kxd2 Nc6 15. Nf3 $16 {Much better
position for white.. h7 pawn is constantly under attack and d4 pawn is very
weak. we are going to take it soon or later}) 9. Qxd5 $14 {And white gets a
pawn...}) 5. Qxd2 Bf5 6. e3 h6 {Black need to play h6 soon or later, cause,
our bishop prevents e6} 7. Bf4 e6 {His light bishop is quite strong, so we
want to exchange bishops} 8. Bd3 Bxd3 9. Qxd3 c5 (9... Bd6 10. Ne2 Bxf4 11.
Nxf4 {It's already unpleasant position for black.. Nh5 is serious threat. Also,
black can't play c5 because of the Qb5+} Nd7 12. O-O-O Qe7 13. Kb1 O-O-O 14. h5
$1 {Important move. White fixes h6 pawn. White should play c4 or e4 and he
will have better position}) 10. c3 Nc6 11. Nf3 Bd6 12. dxc5 Bxc5 13. O-O-O {In
the case of 0-0 we are going to play g4 straightaway} O-O (13... Qa5 14. Kb1
O-O-O 15. Nd4 $14 {And white is slightly better thanks to the space advantage.
We are going to play h5 to block his pawns on the kingside and e4 or c4 in one
moment to open up the center}) 14. g4 $40 {And white has strong attack} *

